==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: mercury bichloride
<hw>mercury bichloride</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>the compound
(<chform>HgCl2</chform>) consisting of two atoms of chlorine united with
one atom of mercury. Also called <altname>bichloride of
mercury</altname>, <altname>mercuric chloride</altname>,
<altname>corrosive sublimate</altname>, and <altname>mercury
perchloride</altname>. It is used as ⟦ldquo⟧a topical antiseptic and
disinfectant for inanimate objects⟦rdquo⟧.</def> <au>Stedman's
25th</au>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>mercury fulminate</ent>⟦br⟧
